20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
21 as follows:
22 Article – Transportation
23 3–216.
24 (a) There is a Transportation Trust Fund for the Department.
25 (c) (2) (i) The Gasoline and Motor Vehicle Revenue Account, the Driver
26 Education Account, the Motorcycle Safety Program Account, [and] the Transportation
27 Network Company Impact Fee Account, AND THE HIGHWAY USE FEE ACCOUNT shall
28 be maintained in the Transportation Trust Fund.
29 (d) (6) (I) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ALLOCATE THE FUNDS IN THE
30 HIGHWAY USE FEE ACCOUNT SOLELY FOR THE NEEDS OF THE MARYLAND AREA
31 REGIONAL COMMUTER RAIL SERVICE.
32 (II) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, THE
33 FUNDS IN THE HIGHWAY USE FEE ACCOUNT MAY NOT BE TRANSFERRED OR
34 DIVERTED TO THE GENERAL FUND OF THE STATE OR USED FOR ANY OTHER
35 PURPOSE WITHIN THE DEPARTMENT.

