5 11–103.4.
6 “ALTERNATIVE FUEL VEHICLE” MEANS A MOTOR VEHICLE THAT:
7 (1) IS MANUFACTURED OR MODIFIED TO USE AN ALTERNATIVE FUEL,
8 INCLUDING ELECTRICITY, ETHANOL, METHANOL, GASOHOL, AND PROPANE OR
9 NATURAL GAS, REGARDLESS OF ENERGY CONSUMPTION; AND
10 (2) IS NOT A MOTOR FUEL VEHICLE, PLUG–IN ELECTRIC DRIVE
11 VEHICLE, OR PLUG–IN HYBRID VEHICLE.
12 11–125.2.
13 “FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE” MEANS A MOTOR VEHICLE THAT HAS A
14 COMBINED FUEL ECONOMY RATING OF AT LEAST 25 MILES PER GALLON.
15 [13–956.
