8 13–956.
9 (A) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO:
10 (1) AN AUTOCYCLE, MOPED, OR MOTORCYCLE;
11 (2) A VEHICLE WITH A GROSS WEIGHT OVER 26,000 POUNDS;
12 (3) A VEHICLE THAT IS OWNED BY A GOVERNMENTAL ENTITY;
13 (4) A VEHICLE THAT IS REGISTERED UNDER THE INTERNATIONAL
14 REGISTRATION PLAN; OR
15 (5) A VEHICLE THAT PARTICIPATES IN THE MILEAGE–BASED USER
16 FEE PROGRAM ESTABLISHED UNDER § 13–957 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
17 (B) IN ADDITION TO THE REGISTRATION FEE OTHERWISE REQUIRED BY
18 THIS TITLE, THE OWNER OF AN ALTERNATIVE FUEL VEHICLE, A FUEL–EFFICIENT
19 VEHICLE, OR A PLUG–IN ELECTRIC DRIVE VEHICLE SHALL PAY AN ANNUAL HIGHWAY
20 USE FEE FOR EACH MOTOR VEHICLE REGISTERED.
21 (C) THE HIGHWAY USE FEE SHALL BE:
22 (1) CALCULATED IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS
23 SECTION;
24 (2) COLLECTED BY THE DEPARTMENT AT THE TIME OF VEHICLE
25 REGISTRATION; AND
26 (3) DEPOSITED IN THE HIGHWAY USE FEE ACCOUNT IN THE
27 TRANSPORTATION TRUST FUND.
28 (D) (1) (I) THE SECRETARY SHALL CALCULATE THE HIGHWAY USE FEE
29 IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SUBSECTION.

HOUSE BILL 1374 5
1 (II) FOR PURPOSES OF ESTIMATING THE AMOUNT OF MOTOR
2 FUEL TAXES PAID EACH YEAR TO OPERATE A FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE UNDER THIS
3 SUBSECTION, THE SECRETARY SHALL:
4 1. ESTIMATE THE AVERAGE NUMBER OF MILES A CLASS
5 A VEHICLE TRAVELS IN THE STATE EACH YEAR;
6 2. CALCULATE THE NUMBER OF GALLONS OF FUEL A
7 FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE USES TO TRAVEL THE ESTIMATED NUMBER OF MILES
8 UNDER ITEM 1 OF THIS SUBPARAGRAPH; AND
9 3. APPLY THE MOTOR FUEL TAX RATE ESTABLISHED
10 UNDER § 9–305(A)(2) OF THE TAX – GENERAL ARTICLE AS INCREASED BY THE
11 COMPTROLLER UNDER §§ 9–305(B) AND 9–306 OF THE TAX – GENERAL ARTICLE.
12 (2) FOR A PLUG–IN ELECTRIC DRIVE VEHICLE, THE ANNUAL
13 HIGHWAY USE FEE IS EQUAL TO 85% OF THE ESTIMATED AMOUNT OF MOTOR FUEL
14 TAXES PAID EACH YEAR TO OPERATE A FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE IN THE STATE.
15 (3) (I) FOR AN ALTERNATIVE FUEL VEHICLE OR A
16 FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE, THE ANNUAL HIGHWAY USE FEE IS EQUAL TO 85% OF
17 THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN:
18 1. THE ESTIMATED AMOUNT OF MOTOR FUEL TAXES
19 PAID EACH YEAR TO OPERATE A FUEL–EFFICIENT VEHICLE IN THE STATE; AND
20 2. THE ESTIMATED AMOUNT OF MOTOR FUEL TAXES
21 PAID EACH YEAR TO OPERATE THE VEHICLE BEING REGISTERED IN THE STATE.
22 (II) 1. FOR THE PURPOSES OF ESTIMATING THE AMOUNT OF
23 MOTOR FUEL TAXES PAID TO OPERATE EACH VEHICLE BEING REGISTERED UNDER
24 SUBPARAGRAPH (I)2 OF THIS PARAGRAPH, THE SECRETARY SHALL USE THE
25 COMBINED FUEL ECONOMY RATING FOR THE MOTOR VEHICLE AS DETERMINED BY
26 THE MANUFACTURER OF THE VEHICLE.
27 2. IF THE SECRETARY IS UNABLE TO DETERMINE THE
28 MANUFACTURER’S FUEL ECONOMY FOR THE VEHICLE, THE SECRETARY SHALL USE
29 THE FINAL ESTIMATE OF AVERAGE FUEL ECONOMY AS DETERMINED BY THE U.S.
30 ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY, OF:
31 A. ALL CARS MANUFACTURED DURING THE SAME
32 MODEL YEAR AS THE VEHICLE;

6 HOUSE BILL 1374
1 B. IF THE VEHICLE HAS A GROSS WEIGHT OF AT LEAST
2 6,000 POUNDS BUT LESS THAN 26,000 POUNDS, ALL TRUCKS MANUFACTURED
3 DURING THE SAME MODEL YEAR; OR
4 C. IF DATA IS NOT AVAILABLE FOR THE MODEL YEAR OF
5 THE VEHICLE BEING REGISTERED, AVAILABLE DATA FOR THE MOST RECENT MODEL
6 YEAR CLOSEST TO THE MODEL YEAR OF THE VEHICLE BEING REGISTERED.
7 (E) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, AND EACH JULY 1 THEREAFTER, THE
8 SECRETARY SHALL UPDATE THE HIGHWAY USE FEE CALCULATED UNDER THIS
9 SECTION.
10 (F) IF THE VEHICLE IS REGISTERED FOR A PERIOD OTHER THAN 1 YEAR,
11 THE HIGHWAY USE FEE SHALL BE MULTIPLIED BY THE NUMBER OF YEARS OR
12 FRACTION OF YEARS THAT THE VEHICLE WILL BE REGISTERED.
13 (G) IF A PERSON THAT OWNS A MOTOR VEHICLE SUBJECT TO THE HIGHWAY
14 USE FEE FAILS TO PAY THE FEE, THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL REFUSE TO REGISTER
15 OR RENEW OR TRANSFER THE REGISTRATION OF THE MOTOR VEHICLE.
16 13–957.
17 (A) (1) THERE IS A VOLUNTARY MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM
18 IN THE DEPARTMENT.
19 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM IS
20 TO ALLOW THE OWNER OF A VEHICLE SUBJECT TO THE HIGHWAY USE FEE
21 ESTABLISHED UNDER § 13–956 OF THIS SUBTITLE TO PAY A MILEAGE–BASED USER
22 FEE IN LIEU OF THE HIGHWAY USE FEE.
23 (B) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH PROCEDURES FOR THE
24 COLLECTION OF THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE ON AN ANNUAL BASIS.
25 (2) FROM THE AMOUNT OF THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE
26 COLLECTED EACH YEAR, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL RETAIN AN AMOUNT NECESSARY
27 TO ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM AND DEPOSIT THE REMAINDER IN THE HIGHWAY
28 USE FEE ACCOUNT OF THE TRANSPORTATION TRUST FUND.
29 (C) (1) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1 OF THE YEAR FOLLOWING THE YEAR THE
30 DEPARTMENT ESTABLISHES THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM, AND
31 EACH JULY 1 THEREAFTER, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL CALCULATE THE

HOUSE BILL 1374 7
1 MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE FOR THE FISCAL YEAR AS PROVIDED IN THIS
2 SUBSECTION.
3 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL CALCULATE A FEE PER MILE DRIVEN BY
4 DIVIDING THE HIGHWAY USE FEE UNDER § 13–956 OF THIS SUBTITLE BY THE
5 ESTIMATED AVERAGE NUMBER OF MILES A CLASS A VEHICLE TRAVELS IN THE
6 STATE EACH YEAR.
7 (3) THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE IS EQUAL TO THE NUMBER OF
8 MILES A PARTICIPANT’S VEHICLE TRAVELS DURING THE FISCAL YEAR MULTIPLIED
9 BY THE FEE PER MILE DRIVEN CALCULATED UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
10 SUBSECTION.
11 (D) THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PAID BY A MOTOR VEHICLE OWNER MAY
12 NOT EXCEED THE ANNUAL HIGHWAY USE FEE THAT THE OWNER WOULD HAVE
13 OTHERWISE PAID UNDER § 13–956 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
14 (E) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH POLICIES AND PROCEDURES TO
15 ALLOW OWNERS OF VEHICLES SUBJECT TO THE HIGHWAY USE FEE THE OPTION OF
16 PARTICIPATING IN THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM WITH VEHICLE
17 LOCATION AND DATA TRACKING LIMITATIONS, INCLUDING:
18 (1) THE REQUIREMENT THAT ANY DATA COLLECTED BE USED ONLY
19 FOR ADMINISTRATION OF THE PROGRAM;
20 (2) THE EXCLUSION OF ANY INDIVIDUAL PARTICIPANT DATA FROM
21 DISCLOSURE;
22 (3) THE REQUIREMENT THAT PROGRAM DATA HAVE A SPECIFIC AND
23 LIMITED DATA RETENTION PERIOD; AND
24 (4) THE REQUIREMENT THAT ANY RESEARCH USING AGGREGATED
25 DATA BE SUBJECT TO THE APPROVAL OF AN INSTITUTIONAL REVIEW BOARD.
26 (F) THE OWNER OF A MOTOR VEHICLE REGISTERED IN THE STATE MAY NOT
27 BE REQUIRED TO PARTICIPATE IN THE MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM.
28 (G) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2029, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH A
29 FULLY OPERATIONAL MILEAGE–BASED USER FEE PROGRAM.
30 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
31 1, 2026.

